Not hating, but it’s not a BLEVE pronounced “blevy”. A BLEVE is when a compressed gas/ liquid is heated from the outside of the cylinder and the liquid boils, triggers the pressure relief device. It doesn’t explode at first because the boiling propane/ compressed gas acts as a coolant when it evaporates and escapes through the pressure relief valve.  Once the propane liquid has evaporated to a certain point, the pressure builds past the capabilities of the pressure relief valve and the cylinder explodes.
